50|$|In genetics, <b>gene</b> <b>drive</b> is the {{phenomenon}} {{in which the}} inheritance of a particular gene or set of genes is favorably biased. <b>Gene</b> <b>drive</b> can arise {{through a variety of}} mechanisms and results in its prevalence increasing in a population. Engineered gene drives have been proposed to provide an effective means of genetically modifying populations or even whole species.|$|E
50|$|There are {{bioethics}} {{concerns as}} well, as the <b>gene</b> <b>drive</b> {{is a very}} powerful tool.|$|E
